and","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"before 1158–1205":"before 1158–1205","1158–1205":"1158–1205","1156–1224":"1156–1224","1175–1262":"1175–1262","1153–Female":"1153–Deceased","1125–1188":"1125–1188","1130–Female":"1130–Deceased","before 1158":"before 1158","1153":"1153","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1262":"1262","1181":"1181","1205":"1205","1125":"1125","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1156":"1156","1188":"1188","after 1188":"after 1188","about 1175":"about 1175","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, England","Freiston, Lincolnshire, England":"Freiston, Lincolnshire, England","Headington, Oxfordshire, England":"Headington, Oxfordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Craon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Manx: variant of   Craine  .","English: variant of   Crane  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Craine","meanings":["Manx: shortened form of Gaelic <b>Mac (Giolla) Ciaráin</b> ‘son of (the devotee of) <i>Ciarán</i>’, a personal name based on a diminutive of Gaelic <i>ciar</i>, Manx <i>keeir</i> ‘black’. The place Ballacraine on the Isle of Man means ‘Craine's farm’."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guy de Craon II was born before 1158, in Freiston, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Maurice de Craon, Lord of Freiston, was 33 and his mother, Clarice, was 28. He married Isabel Basset in 1181, in Headington, Oxfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1205, in Pentney, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"before 1158–1205":"enne 1158–1205","1158–1205":"1158–1205","1156–1224":"1156–1224","1175–1262":"1175–1262","1153–Female":"1153–Surnud","1125–1188":"1125–1188","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","before 1158":"enne 1158","1153":"1153","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1262":"1262","1181":"1181","1205":"1205","1125":"1125","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1156":"1156","1188":"1188","after 1188":"pärast 1188","about 1175":"umbes 1175","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, England","Freiston, Lincolnshire, England":"Freiston, Lincolnshire, England","Headington, Oxfordshire, England":"Headington, Oxfordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"before 1158–1205":"ennen vuotta 1158–1205","1158–1205":"1158–1205","1156–1224":"1156–1224","1175–1262":"1175–1262","1153–Female":"1153–Kuollut","1125–1188":"1125–1188","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","before 1158":"ennen vuotta 1158","1153":"1153","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1262":"1262","1181":"1181","1205":"1205","1125